Usage: g2o_simulator2d [options] [graph-output]

General options:
-------------------------------------------
-help / -h           Displays this help.

Program Options:
-------------------------------------------
-hasCompass                  the robot has a compass
-hasGPS                      the robot has a GPS
-hasOdom                     the robot has an odometry
-hasPointBearingSensor       the robot has a point bearing sensor
-hasPointSensor              the robot has a point sensor
-hasPoseSensor               the robot has a pose sensor
-hasSegmentSensor            the robot has a segment sensor
-maxSegmentLenght <double>   maximal lenght of a segment in the world (default: 3)
-minSegmentLenght <double>   minimal lenght of a segment in the world (default: 0.5)
-nSegments <int>             number of segments (default: 1000)
-nlandmarks <int>            number of landmarks in the map (default: 100)
-segmentGridSize <int>       number of cells of the grid where to align the segments (default: 50)
-simSteps <int>              number of simulation steps (default: 100)
-worldSize <double>          size of the world (default: 25)

